---
alwaysApply: true
---
- Use RESTful API design principles with proper HTTP methods: GET (read), POST (create), PUT/PATCH (update), DELETE (remove).
- Structure API endpoints using nouns, not verbs: /users, /messages, /conversations.
- Use nested resources for related entities: /users/{id}/messages.
- Implement consistent response format with data envelope: { success: boolean, data: any, error?: string }.
- Use proper HTTP status codes: 200 OK, 201 Created, 400 Bad Request, 401 Unauthorized, 403 Forbidden, 404 Not Found, 500 Internal Server Error.
- Implement request validation using Zod or Joi before processing.
- Return appropriate error messages that help client-side debugging without exposing internals.
- Implement pagination with consistent cursor/limit/offset patterns.
- Use query parameters for filtering, sorting, and field selection.
- Version APIs using URL prefix: /api/v1/, /api/v2/.
- Document all endpoints with clear descriptions of request/response formats.
- Implement WebSocket endpoints for real-time features (chat notifications).
- Use consistent naming conventions for API endpoints (kebab-case or camelCase).
- Return timestamps in ISO 8601 format (UTC preferred).
- Implement request ID tracking for debugging and logging correlation.
